<section id="log_dialog_general">
<title>General information</title>
<p>
When opened via the "Show logs ..." menu entry the log dialog shows all input and output characters generated by the simulated machine.
It looks like this: 
</p>
<media type="image" src="log_dialog.png"/>
<p>
The default grouping used when displaying input and output characters depends on the mode (Encipher/Decipher) the machine is in. The
default grouping used in the Encipher mode mode is "No Grouping" for input and "Group by 5" for output. In Decipher mode it is the other
way round.
</p>

<note><p>
For machines which allow switching between a letters and a figures mode some input characters do only generate output characters. Or in 
other words: The characters used to switch between letters and figures are not shown in the "Input log" part of the dialog.
</p></note>
